1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the construction and determination of parameters of linear codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the construction of codes with flexible parameters, which may involve computational complexity considerations. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions applications of the constructed codes in secret sharing schemes, which is a topic related to cryptography and security. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve the use of algorithms and data structures in the construction and determination of parameters of the linear codes. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper may involve the use of combinatorial techniques in the construction and determination of parameters of the linear codes, as well as in the applications to combinational designs.
